@SerhiiBilyk thanks for reaching out!

the related code is the fixer function:  https://github.com/eslint/eslint/blob/5da378ac922d732ca1765f08edee0face1b1b924/lib/rules/no-else-return.js#L63-L64

it should return `null`, if not safe to do the fix.

@Aladdin-ADD can you check the algorithm?
I'm cheking if there block scope local variable declaration inside [else] statement.
If [true], fix is unsafe => return null

Is this correct?
P.S. startToken && endToken of ELSE block

```js
const isScopeDeclaration = (token) => {
  const keyword = token.type === 'Keyword';
  const scopeDeclaration = token.value === 'let' || token.value === 'const';
  return keyword && scopeDeclaration;
};
const isDeclarationInside = sourceCode.getTokensBetween(startToken, endToken).findIndex(isScopeDeclaration) > -1;
```
